31/01/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Justice Minister Meri Mladenovska-Gorgievska said Friday (28 January) that draft constitutional changes aimed at reforming the judicial sector and increasing the courts' independence would be ready by April.
She said the ministry already has formed an expert team to come up with proposals for constitutional amendments.
The team includes representatives of all judicial institutions and parties in parliament.
In other news, Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski kicked off a two-day visit to Belgrade on Monday.
He will meet both Serbian and federal union officials to discuss boosting bilateral ties.
(A1 TV, Beta - 30/01/05;
Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 29/01/05)
